>>>	tutorial_wincondition			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>ignore_for_progress
>background	hidden
>layout	duo	zoe,liam
	zoe	eyebrows	Wait a second, champ!
	liam	default	Yeah, no need to rush into this. We're here to give you some tips on how to do cons the right way.
	zoe	naughty	Think of it like... some sort of tutorial!
	liam	bored	(God knows you could use one of those...)
	zoe	hyped	As everyone knows, the main activity of a con is... finding love.
	liam	suspicious	Eh...
	zoe	happy	Yeah, I know, it isn't really; but this is %CURRENTPLAYERNAME% we're talking about.
	zoe	naughty	Look at %HIMHER%: %HESHE% %VERB_IS_ARE% probably aiming to get a date at the big con afterparty.	
	player	default	...
	liam	bored	Ah, yes... the silence speaks volumes.
	zoe	happy	Well, if you wanna get a date, you'd better get to know the other person and what they look for in a potential partner.
	liam	talking	Exactly: do they share dreams and fears? Are your visions of the world in sync? Are your souls truly compatible?
	zoe	happy	Too complicated! Let's say someone's personality can be defined through five traits: SMARTS; BOLDNESS; CREATIVITY; CHARM; and FUN.
	zoe	excited	Let's call them STATS! It sounds cooler and more videogame-y.
	liam	thinking	A tad reductive, but let's work with that.
	zoe	default	Then you have to ask yourself: is your FUN high enough for someone who loves to party? Is your BOLDNESS low enough for someone who likes peace and quiet?
	liam	glasses	Sometimes people are even more ambiguous... like they may like someone who's just... balanced.
	zoe	hyped	The point is, everyone has their standards... stat standards!
	liam	talking	And if by some chance you want to go to the party by yourself...
	zoe	happy	(Which is a totally valid option if that's your jam!)
	liam	smile	...don't think you'll be exempt from managing your stats. You can still fail at it!
	zoe	default	There's more stuff to keep in mind... but let's cover that later, okay? There was a panel I wanted to check out.
	liam	thinking	Sounds good. And I have to rehearse the next "tutorial".
	zoe	laugh	Have fun, %CURRENTPLAYERNAME%!

>>>	tutorial_statexchange			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>ignore_for_progress
>background	hidden
>layout	duo	zoe,liam
	zoe	intense	Wait a second! It's time for a new episode of "Tutorials with Liam and Zoe"!
	liam	default	Yes. We realized we have explained the importance of managing stats; but we didn't cover how to manage them properly.
	zoe	excited	Exactly! Stats can be managed in a number of ways. But let's cover the most important one!
	liam	smile	That'd be experiencing the sort of absurd and exciting adventures that usually take place once you visit a LOCATION.
	zoe	happy	Let's call these experiences EVENTS, for short.
	liam	thinking	Normally, during an EVENT, you face a conflict you must solve by choosing between potential solutions... OPTIONS, if you will.
	liam	default	What you choose will define you as a person. If you choose a SMART OPTION, you'll gain SMARTS.
	zoe	laugh	Yeah! If you choose to punch a bear, that'd be quite bold of you, so you'd gain BOLDNESS.
	liam	default	But STATS are also lost when choosing an OPTION.
	liam	glasses	Every path not taken is a stat lost.
	zoe	default	Which is to say: if you chose the SMART OPTION instead of punching the bear, then you'd gain SMARTS but lose BOLDNESS.
	liam	bored	Just... try not to punch a bear, okay?
	zoe	naughty	Liam, let %CURRENTPLAYERNAME% punch a bear if that's who %HESHE% %VERB_IS_ARE% as a person.
	liam	thinking	Anyway, there are a few more ways of managing STATS, like...
	zoe	intense	Liam, let's write those down in a MANUAL or something. I really wanted to go check out those limited figurines I told you about.
	liam	talking	True. We can keep giving you tips later, yes? In the meantime, don't get yourself killed.

>>>	tutorial_statsglossarya			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>ignore_for_progress
>background	hidden
>layout	duo	zoe,liam
	zoe	intense	Stop right there! This is the STAT police! We're here to test you on your STAT knowledge.
	zoe	laugh	Just kiddin'! It's us: Zoe and Liam, renowned creators, verified hot people, and knowledgeable tutorial dispensers!
	liam	thinking	We thought, "We've been giving %CURRENTPLAYERNAME% all these exquisite tips on how to manage STATS; but how easy is it to know which OPTION ties to which STAT?"
	zoe	default	Yeah! Some OPTIONS will be easy to interpret, like how punching a bear feels like a very BOLD thing to do.
	liam	eyeroll	But some will be quite a bit more nuanced, and it might be harder to tie them to a STAT...
	zoe	happy	...which is why we've written all the specifics to every STAT in a MANUAL for you to check!
	narrator		(Which will be available within the CUSTOMIZE menu.)
	liam	default	So even if an OPTION might not feel tied to a specific STAT, or even more than one...
	liam	thinking	...you just gotta take your time. Try to analyze what's the biggest clue within the OPTION, and which STAT relates to that specific clue.
	zoe	hyped	Or you know what? Just ignore STATS and choose whichever OPTION feels more interesting to you. Live, fail, have fun!
	liam	smile	I must agree with Zoe here. Just try not to fail TOO MUCH.
	zoe	naughty	Meh... let's go play some DDR so I can see YOU fail TOO MUCH.
	liam	eyeroll	Tch... let's go; but don't be surprised if you're disappointed.
	zoe	excited	See ya around, %CURRENTPLAYERNAME%!

>>>	tutorial_foodcourt			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>ignore_for_progress
>background	hidden
>layout	solo	narratorbody
	narratorbody	happy	Welcome to the Food Court! You'll be visiting this place twice per run.
	narratorbody	happy	Ah, yes, this tutorial will be delivered by me, The Narrator!
	narratorbody	cat	Tutorials explained by characters are fun and immersive; but as the Narrator, I have the power to go straight to the point!
>line_requirement	platform	!console
	narratorbody	smile	For example, I can just tell you that by pressing "TAB" you can access useful info!
>line_requirement	platform	switch
	narratorbody	smile	For example, I can just tell you that by pressing "ZL/SL" you can access useful info!
>line_requirement	platform	playstation
	narratorbody	smile	For example, I can just tell you that by pressing "L2" you can access useful info!
>line_requirement	platform	xbox
	narratorbody	smile	For example, I can just tell you that by pressing "LT" you can access useful info!
>line_requirement	platform	!console
	narratorbody	smile	Or that you can consult the dialogue history by either pressing "H" or "mousewheel up".
>line_requirement	platform	switch
	narratorbody	smile	Or that you can consult the dialogue history by pressing "X".
>line_requirement	platform	playstation
	narratorbody	smile	Or that you can consult the dialogue history by pressing the triangle button.
>line_requirement	platform	xbox
	narratorbody	smile	Or that you can consult the dialogue history by pressing "Y".
	narratorbody	happy	Cool, huh?
	narratorbody	default	Anyhow, back to the Food Court!
	narratorbody	default	Food Court turns are about getting to know the one person you want to take to the con afterparty, even if that means getting to know yourself.
	narratorbody	default	There are 5 tables you can choose from.
	narratorbody	default	3 of the tables are populated by the 6 Romance Options, in pairs.
	narratorbody	kiss	One of the tables lets you call one of several "guests", who are essentially alternative date options!
	narratorbody	default	Finally, there's a table for you to sit alone.
	narratorbody	smile	These tables are tied to their own mechanics. As usual, our jam is obscuring said mechanics a bit so you can focus on the narrative side of this experience.
	narratorbody	smile	By playing, you can slowly but steadily learn how everything works.
	narratorbody	smile	But if that's not your style, we've added helpful explanations of everything in the MANUAL. Feel free to check it out!
	narratorbody	default	Just keep in mind that each table only allows for one player.
	narratorbody	happy	Now, go choose a seat!

>>>	tutorial_foodcourtpeppers			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>ignore_for_progress
>background	hidden
>layout	solo	narratorbody
	narratorbody	kiss	So you want to go on a date, huh?
	narratorbody	default	As we've said, these mechanics are covered in the MANUAL; but there's one little thing we wanted to cover here.
	narratorbody	default	You'll see some PEPPERS on the different DATES. They are a sort of "Spicy Meter".
	narratorbody	default	This is like declaring your preference of spiciness when you're pursuing a date. It doesn't affect the date itself, but the ending you'll get if you succeed.
	narratorbody	surprised	The art might be the same, but the narrative won't!
	narratorbody	smile	Zero peppers will make the ending more platonic.
	narratorbody	happy	One and two peppers will make the ending somewhere between romantic and suggestive.
	narratorbody	kiss	Three peppers will make the ending definitively... naughty.
	narratorbody	surprised	Just keep in mind that choosing a low amount of peppers won't affect the content of SECRET ENDINGS, which might be naughty!
	narratorbody	smile	Okay, you're now truly prepared to go on your first date!

>>>	tutorial_gueststable			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>ignore_for_progress
>background	hidden
>layout	solo	narratorbody
	narratorbody	smile	Welcome back to the FOOD COURT!
	narratorbody	default	I wanted to cover the last two important facts about this place: CONVERSATIONS and GUESTS.
	narratorbody	default	The first one is fairly simple: if you sit with the same Romance Option twice in the same run, you'll bond over a conversation.
	narratorbody	surprised	If you sit alone twice, you'll have some you-time to sit and reflect on life and stuff. It's like a CONVERSATION... but with yourself!
	narratorbody	smile	Each PLAYABLE CHARACTER has one of these!
	narratorbody	default	And what about the GUESTS? I wanted to tell you there's three things you gotta do if you want to get a date with one of them.
	narratorbody	default	First, you have to meet their date requirements by the end of the run.
	narratorbody	smile	You'll have clues for what these requirements are when you first greet the GUEST and they tell you what their "type" is.
	narratorbody	three	Second, you gotta have a fun little date with them, to get know each other better.
	narratorbody	default	This is done by calling them a second time when you come back to the FOOD COURT.
	narratorbody	smile	Third, remember to choose "NONE OF THEM" when you're asked which ROMANCE OPTION you want to date at the end of the run!
	narratorbody	smile	And that'd be all.
	narratorbody	happy	Now, let's go sit somewhere!

>>>	tutorial_comics			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>ignore_for_progress
>background	hidden
>layout	duo	zoe,liam
	zoe	hyped	It's time to work on the COMIC!
	liam	glasses	As your creative mentors, we've prepared very original questions that will spur extraordinary ideas!
	zoe	default	We've written two per day.
	liam	smile	You're welcome.
	zoe	default	Once the exercise is done, you might see no comic... just yet.
	liam	talking	But you have to trust the process, %CURRENTPLAYERNAME%; your efforts will come to fruition by the end of the con.
	zoe	laugh	Totally! How you choose to answer the exercises will impact the script of the resulting COMIC!
	zoe	happy	I recommend that you remember (or even take note of) every OPTION you choose during this exercise, to better savor its impact once we get to see the resulting COMIC.
	liam	talking	And there's more to these exercises: all these choices will shape you as a person...
	zoe	intense	...which is to say they will affect your STATS!
	liam	default	You'll feel these changes each time you solve one of the exercises.
	liam	smile	And there's one last thing I love about creative work: when several people collaborate, it changes them all as a group.
	zoe	happy	That's right! My personal advice is that, even if one person is answering an exercise, the whole group should discuss it.
	narrator		To be clear: you'll gain a lot of the STAT tied to the chosen OPTION... but you'll lose the STATS tied to the OPTIONS not chosen.
	narrator		And these STAT effects will equally affect ALL PLAYERS.
	liam	suspicious	Shush that voice! It's breaking the immersion. Ugh.
	zoe	intense	Anyway... enough procrastinating!
	liam	smile	Zoe is right: it's time to work on your craft. Hold this pencil and let the mind wander!

