>>>	tutorial_plotlines			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>ignore_for_progress
>background	hidden
>layout	solo	narratorbody
	narratorbody	smile	So you're in the middle of a PLOTLINE, huh?
	narratorbody	happy	I'm here to explain a small twist.
	narratorbody	default	Normally, when choosing an OPTION in an EVENT, you will gain the STAT associated with that OPTION (and lose the STAT associated with the other OPTION), right?
	narratorbody	happy	(Hope you were paying attention to the other tutorials!)
	narratorbody	default	Well, the LAST EVENT of each PLOTLINE goes back to our classic "STAT THRESHOLD" mechanic from previous games.
	narratorbody	surprised	What does this mean?
	narratorbody	default	In these EVENTS, each OPTION is tied to a STAT. You gotta guess which STAT is tied to each OPTION and then check your own STATS, OK?
	narratorbody	default	Then, if you wanna succeed, you must choose the OPTION tied to your highest STAT of the two.
	narratorbody	happy	If you choose right, congratulations! You'll be one step closer to getting a SECRET ENDING.
	narratorbody	worried	But if you choose wrong? Then you will fail the EVENT, and the PLOTLINE will come to an end, preventing you from getting its SECRET ENDING.
	narratorbody	cat	No pressure, right?
	narratorbody	happy	Nothing else to say. Go for it, player!

>>>	tutorial_shop			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>ignore_for_progress
>background	hidden
>layout	hidden	zorrito
	zorrito	default	Welcome to my humble stand, stranger.
	zorrito	hello	Here, you can get beautiful figurines with amazing properties.
	zorrito	hello	They have all sorts of effects, which you will discover as you unbox them.
	zorrito	default	There are different mystery box categories, each one tied to a different type of effect.
	zorrito	default	(I'll give you some clues on the effect types once you start looking through the boxes.)
	zorrito	default	So, you choose which box category you want, and before you open it, you'll decide if you want to keep it for yourself or give it to a friend.
	zorrito	shady	A balance between order and chaos: you can control which type of effect you want, but you won't know exactly which figurine of that category you'll get.
	zorrito	bummed	And don't fret: if you aren't a fan of surprises at all, there's a category that guarantees NO EFFECT at all.
	zorrito	offering	So: ready for the unboxing?

>>>	tutorial_plotlinedates			
>writer	jules
>event_type	special
>topic_tags
>argument_tags
>ignore_for_progress
>background	hidden
>layout	solo	narratorbody
	narratorbody	smile	Hey, stranger!
	narratorbody	surprised	This is the last TUTORIAL about the FOOD COURT, I promise!
	narratorbody	surprised	Did you notice there were some locked DATES? Those are tied to plotlines!
	narratorbody	default	Some plotlines will first appear organically and catch you by surprise...
	narratorbody	default	...but once you finish them, you'll be able to trigger them again by choosing their respective date.
	narratorbody	surprised	There are also locked PLOTLINE DATES at the ALONE TABLE.
	narratorbody	default	Those do NOT appear organically: you gotta unlock them, and only then you can trigger them through their respective DATES.
	narratorbody	default	PLOTLINE DATES only appear during the first FOOD COURT turn, since you'll need time for the PLOTLINE to fully develop.
	narratorbody	default	Also, they have a "Spicy Meter" to better inform the spiciness of the plotline and its secret ending.
	narratorbody	happy	Anyhow, you must be hungry: go sit somewhere!
